# Presentation Layer Rules

## No hardcoded texts
Every string shown in the UI must be localized via `context.l10n`. Add the key to **all** `.arb` files under `lib/src/core/language/l10n/`.

```dart
// ❌ BAD — current violations in user_config_example_page.dart
Text('Snackbar')
Text('Banner')
BaseSnackbar.success(context, message: 'Route saved successfully')
BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: 'Failed to load route data')

// ✅ GOOD
Text(context.l10n.snackbarSectionTitle)
Text(context.l10n.bannerSectionTitle)
BaseSnackbar.success(context, message: context.l10n.routeSavedSuccessfully)
BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: context.l10n.failedToLoadRouteData)
```

New keys go in every `.arb` file:
```json
// app_en.arb
"snackbarSectionTitle": "Snackbar",
"routeSavedSuccessfully": "Route saved successfully"
```

## No hardcoded colors
- ❌ `Color(0xFF123456)`, `Colors.red`, `Colors.green.shade400`
- ✅ `context.colorScheme.error`, `context.colorScheme.primary`

## Input fields — no TextEditingController
Input state lives in BLoC via `FieldState`. Read value from state, dispatch events on change, show `FieldState.error` when invalid.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — hypothetical user_config display name field
BlocBuilder<UserConfigEditBloc, UserConfigEditState>(
  builder: (context, state) => TextField(
    onChanged: (v) => context.read<UserConfigEditBloc>().add(UserConfigDisplayNameChanged(v)),
    decoration: InputDecoration(
      labelText: context.l10n.displayName,
      errorText: state.displayName.isInvalid ? state.displayName.error : null,
    ),
  ),
)

// ❌ BAD
final _nameController = TextEditingController();
TextField(controller: _nameController)
```

## Failure display
Listen to `state.failure` in a `BlocListener` and display the appropriate component based on `failure.type`.
Always check `failure.message` first; if null, fall back to a localized default via `context.l10n`.

### Component reference

| `FailureType` | Component | Call |
|---------------|-----------|------|
| `snackbar` | `BaseSnackbar` | `BaseSnackbar.error / .warning / .info / .success(context, message:)` |
| `alert` | `BaseDialog` | `BaseDialog.showBasic(context, title:, description:, primaryLabel:)` |
| `fullScreenError` | `BaseDialog` | `BaseDialog.showFullscreen(context, title:, bodyText:, primaryLabel:)` |
| `banner` | `MaterialBanner` | `ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showMaterialBanner(...)` |
| `inlineError` | — | Mapped to `FieldState.error` in BLoC — nothing to do in UI |
| `silent` | — | No UI; log/analytics only |

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — applies to ThemeBloc / LocaleBloc consumers
BlocListener<ThemeBloc, ThemeState>(
  listenWhen: (prev, curr) => curr.failure != null && prev.failure != curr.failure,
  listener: (context, state) {
    final failure = state.failure!;
    final message = failure.message ?? context.l10n.defaultErrorMessage;

    switch (failure.type) {
      case FailureType.snackbar:
        // Choose severity: .error / .warning / .info / .success
        BaseSnackbar.error(context, message: message);

      case FailureType.alert:
        // Blocking modal — user must acknowledge before continuing
        BaseDialog.showBasic(
          context,
          title: context.l10n.errorTitle,
          description: message,
          primaryLabel: context.l10n.ok,
          barrierDismissible: false,
        );

      case FailureType.fullScreenError:
        // Full-screen takeover — for critical, unrecoverable errors
        BaseDialog.showFullscreen(
          context,
          title: context.l10n.errorTitle,
          bodyText: message,
          primaryLabel: context.l10n.retry,
          onPrimary: () => context.read<ThemeBloc>().add(const ThemeStarted()),
          barrierDismissible: false,
        );

      case FailureType.inlineError:
        // Already mapped to FieldState.error in BLoC — nothing to do here
        break;

      case FailureType.silent:
        break;
    }
  },
)
```

## Imports
- ❌ NO imports from any `data/` layer
- ❌ NO imports from another feature's `presentation/` or BLoC directly — rely on DI

## File naming
Files must be prefixed with the feature name:
- ✅ `user_config_example_page.dart`, `user_config_theme_dropdown.dart`
- ❌ `example_page.dart`, `theme_dropdown.dart`
